The paper discusses the application of Software Defined Networking (SDN) in low-power wireless networks, which are a key component of the Internet of Things (IoT). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the reliability and energy-efficiency of the proposed solution, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel architecture for SDN control, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses simulation and experimentation, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
